caption: This place had the best Patty melt I’ve ever had in my life!!! So good. Everything was excellent, and affordable. I highly recommend!
It's been a whole year since I got the pleasure of some Kukhnya. Great food,  great folks running the joint.  Go get some
The only decently priced good food made by punks.
Some of the best inexpensive food in town, and the best burgers, period. I've never been disappointed here.
Food so good like meow!
Was very good food and great atmosphere

This restaurant has a great variety of foods that are geared towards the working class! The food has a flare of which I have never been offered anywhere else. The waitstaff is very explanatory about what the meals consist of. Also they have been nothing but welcoming every time I have eaten there. I enjoy the music variety as well! The environment is laidback and there are local artists showcasing their art within! I will always return especially for the fries and the company!

Well Where should I start... The interior has nothing common with real Ukrainian culture. At the entrance we never been greeted. The waitresses can't pronounce names of the meals in menu. Silverware never been served. Food is disgusting. I ordered blini and salad Olivie. It was cooked probably few weeks ago and defrosted before servings and taste is horrible. Definitely overpriced. When I told the waitress about it, I never got any apology. I feel so bad for my country's unique culture and delicious cuisine, being ashamed of this place. Please don't go there and don't waist your time and money
Great food, great service! Get the perogies!!!

Great service, and amazing food. Literally the only place in the city to get pierogi (AND they're really really good). Doing a great job with COVID restrictions and limited staff. Also, for the high quality of food, the prices are amazing. Love this place.
I'm sure their menu is delicious but I wouldn't know cause I always get the stroganoff 🤷🏻‍♂️
Best thing for people past 4pm on weekdays except on Tuesday. Heard they got brunch. Heard it was banging.
Had 2 different burgers here & they seriously were the best burgers we've ever had. Great service. Clean environment & very welcoming
Plan on the food taking a little time but it is soooo worth the wait and it's super fresh and consistent

No complaints about the food. As others have noted, service and delivery time need lots of work. Ordered a bowl of soup. Still waiting 55 minutes later! No apologies from the server and no comp for the poor kitchen management.
Fabulous food and service that's with the wait. Neighbourhood provides an excellent floor show.
Had the veggie sampler and it was awesome!
The food is simply to die for. Plenty of vegetarian options!
Great music. Neighborhood New Orleans feel. Low prices, high value. Only 4/5 because my shashlik was room temperature when it arrived. Cocktails were good, but not excellent.
It wuz rull goood 👍
Such great food.   I love this place.   The only pierogies in town worth trying.   Great veggie options as well.

I stopped by Monday for an early dinner.  I asked for some recommendations.  They recommended the beet salad and the Slavic sampler.  Both were very good.  My favorite was probably the cabbage with the meat interior.  I will definitely visit again the next time I am in town.

It would be 5 stars for the food. The food is awesome! The service has been getting worse over the last several months. Items forgotten, slow service, food coming out all at once resulting in some of it being cold, and then being asked to leave to seat a new group of people even though we had just ordered a last round of drinks, which the server suggested we take to go.
Cozy little dive with great food. We had kebabs and meatballs, both of which were excellent. Probably our favorite food we had in New Orleans.

Delicious borsch, both vegan and beef, but beef is my favorite. Beef stroganoff was very yummy too. It was nice to have a traditionally home cooked meal. Will be coming back to The Green Room Kukhnya when we’re in town.
Good food and fast, friendly service.
The breakfast food... well all the food I've had here has been outstanding. Just hands down some of the most consistently great food you can get while you're in New Orleans.
Best Russian meal out side of Russia. Make sure to get there.

One of my favorite places in New Orleans, quality food and a great price, everybody’s chill, and those beet juice based bloody Mary’s are insane!!!! The asparagus sides with mustard gosh dang, it’s on a hood street but ultimately one of the best bars I visited out of the 50 I saw in New Orleans, go here and eat everything you’ll be happy, lastly the place is CLEAN
Great menu and food, great prices. Owner and staff really nice.  No other place in New Orleans to get this kinda of food.
The food is just amazing. Lots of options as well, including for vegetarians. The sampler platter is a perfect taste of everything
Picked up some beef stroganoff to go tonight and it was amazing! They have a huge menu selection and decent prices. Definitely will be returning to try this again.
Amazing FOOD!

This has been my favorite spot in New Orleans for over 2 years. I'm leaving tomorrow and decided to have my last dinner in the city here. Truly amazing food at a reasonable price that never disappoints. There's something for everyone so it's one of my favorite places to bring people without having to worry about their dietary restrictions.  My favorite dish is the kielbasa and kapusta, but if it's your first time just get the sampler. I did decide to try the beet burger once and it really does live up to the hype. I hope if you're considering trying this place you'll give it a shot. I can't wait to visit and bring more people here.
My favorite burger in town ♡

Food is good but the service and wait time need a lot of work. Ordered a pick up order and was told it would be ready in 20 minutes. 45 minutes later I'm still sitting in the restaurant waiting for my food to show up. Definitely don't eat here if you have places to be.
I pray to the thin lizzy poster they have in there. Food is solid too.

I love that the menu has ample vegetarian and meat options, one of the few places that my husband and I can both eat and feel satisfied! My favorite veggie dish is the large grilled apple salad, the pirogues (of course) and the Beet Rueben. Prices are affordable, too.
Good foods
Excellent food at a really reasonable price

Very disappointed. Being of russian heritage myself and my wife always trying to taste russian food wherever we can find a restaurant. We did not have some over the top expectations as we would have in Brooklyn or Miami, but this experience was outright disappointing. Between us we ordered soups, salads, appetizers and entrees. After half an hour wait ALL of them have arrived together which is really unheard of. Selection is very limited and while all dishes have russian names none of what we ordered can be counted as authentic russian food, but rather poor imitation.

This place is great, don't pass it up. Awesome, down to earth staff, cool and cozy space. I got the Slovak platter (Non-veg) and everything on it was amazing. The menu is affordable and the portions are a great size. They even have Ukrainian and Russian beers!! Had the Ukrainian beer and it was perfect with the food. Will be back for sure (most definitely when It gets colder too!!)

Bow before the green room and surrender your deepest Slavic culinary fantasies for the cooks, who seem to take sadistic pleasure in delivering to you the most fantastic tasting cuisine. Their reverance for detail, and execution of skill will stun and bewitch you. This local restaurant is highly equipped with a variety of high end ingredients which will mingle joyously with your taste buds. Your loyal servitude begins with one call, or one journey to the church of Green Room Kukhnya.
Delicious food friendly staff
Amazing place. Food was tasty. Services was great. Everything was well managed.

THIS PLACE IS DELICIOUS!  I HIGHLY RECOMMEND THE MEAT GOLUBTSY (MEAT STUFFED CABBAGE ROLLS) & THE BEET BURGER!!  YUM.  THEY HAVE A HUGE MENU SO I CAN'T WAIT TO GO BACK TO TRY OTHER ITEMS...THANK YOU!!!
Authentic food, just like in Mother Russia!!!
Always amazing. If youre on the fence, go. If youre trying to decide  between a few places... knock it off... go here.
Not bad! Great atmosphere with some cool artwork on the walls. Staff were friendly and food was good!
One of my favorite places in the city. Best Reuben in town.  Sorry Dan Stein.  Edit...  Their service has gotten worse and worse lately

This has to be first or second best restaurant for vegitarians in NOLA: sooo many options! Amazing value, all the portions are large and easily shareable. The St. Bernard vibe won't be for everyone, but we love it. They also have Bison Grass vodka, which is worth the trip alone.

Awesome beyond 5 star restaurant. All food dishes we have tried are so tasty, delicious. Crave this food! Going to get myself some Green Room deliciousness right now! Love supporting the small little businesses! Used to love their food when they had the restaurant in the back of Siberia on St Claude!! Highly recommend. :)
Perogies and blinis were very good
Got the beet burger and veggie burger. Phenomenal!

(Translated by Google) Very good restaurant. Very affordable price. The neighborhood may surprise but no worries. We had dinner for 35 Usd and eat Polish specialties. To recommend.  (Original) Très bon restaurant. Tarif très abordable. Le quartier peut surprendre mais aucun soucis. On a pu dîner pour 35 Usd et manger des spécialités polonaises. A recommander.
I'd fight you for the pierogies, but I don't have to, because they are for sale.

The GreenRoomNOLA is awesome. I have utterly enjoyed every morsel of food on the menu. I feel so lucky to have such a delicious restaurant in the neighborhood. I give the #GreenRoomNOLA the best stars 5 starz ever.
Best food in town. Killer pirogues and bilinis
New location for KUKHNYA which used to be the food window at Siberia for many many years. Outstanding Eastern European food at unbelievably reasonable prices. Best staff.
The food is awesome and the staff is too.
Good food
Great food.  Delicious.   And very reasonably priced.  Will definitely be back.

Great food, reasonably priced, and completely unique to Nola, check out The Green Room on St. Bernard Ave. Across from The Goat for a meal any day except Tuesday. The menu is Russian and Slavic and theres a lot of options. Staff was really friendly and helpful.

Had a plate of Pirogies and a big Czech beer, which were very tasty, but the service was rather poor that evening; I had to fetch both silverware & napkin and salt & pepper from behind the bar myself, for if I had waited until the extremely inattentive barmaid finally looked my way again, the food would likely have been cold, maybe even moldy.
Great food and cocktails. Very affordable and the portions are pretty big too!
Amazing
Delicious, affordable
